South Korea Stocks: Asiana Airlines, Samsung, SK Communications

-- B y   S a e r o m i   S h i n
-- 
2011-07-29T07:17:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-29/south-korea-stocks-asiana-airlines-samsung-sk-communications.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  South Korea  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 3 p.m. close in Seoul.  The  Kospi Index (KOSPI)  fell 22.64, or 1.1 percent, to 2,133.21.
The gauge rose 1.6 percent in July, its first monthly gain since
April.  Asiana Airlines (020560)  Inc. (020560 KS), South Korea’s second-
largest carrier, lost 4.1 percent to 10,600 won, the lowest
close since July 12. The company said the crash of its Boeing
Co. 747-400 freighter caused 200.4 billion won ($190 million) of
damage based on the book value of the aircraft. The plane is
insured for $122 million under an agreement with eight insurance
companies, according to a filing.  Samsung Electronics Co. (005930 KS),  Asia ’s biggest maker
of chips, flat screens and mobile phones, rose 0.8 percent to
844,000 won. The company said net income fell to 3.51 trillion
won in the three months ended June from 4.28 trillion won a year
earlier, according to a statement. Profit beat the 3.4 trillion
won average of 21 analyst estimates compiled by Bloomberg.  SK Communications Co. (066270 KS), an  Internet service
provider , retreated 4.3 percent to 16,650 won. The stock lost 6
percent yesterday after the South Korean telecommunications
regulator said hackers accessed data on 35 million people, more
than half the country’s population, on the company’s websites.  SK Innovation Co. (096770 KS), South Korea’s biggest oil
refiner, decreased 2 percent to 218,000 won, halting a three-day
advance. Net income fell 29 percent to 262.8 billion won in the
three months ended June 30 from a revised 369.4 billion won a
year earlier, according to a filing. That was less than the mean
estimate of 503 billion won of three analysts in a Bloomberg
survey.  To contact the reporter on this story:
